T1  - The Hamilton model with a general autoregressive component: estimation and comparison with other models of economic time series: Estimation and comparison with other models of economic time series
AU  - Lam, Pok-sang
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 26
IS  - 3
SP  - 409
EP  - 432
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/12/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(90)90005-O
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329090005O
AB  - This paper generalizes the Hamilton model to the important case in which the autoregressive component need not contain a unit root. Using U.S. quarterly real GNP data, the model is estimated and the results are compared to those of Hamilton. Some Monte Carlo evidence for the model is presented, and its in-sample forecasting performance is discussed and compared to the original Hamilton model, the ARIMA model, and the deterministic-time-trend model.
