AB  - This note shows how the Beveridge-Nelson decomposition of economic time series can be precisely computed without the necessity for truncating infinite sums. The algorithm includes those of Beveridge and Nelson (1981) and Miller (1988) as special cases for particular models, correcting an error in the latter.
